#: 0b71bb1e9fd74b59bcf31c8b97dcef5b
msgid "Using named disposables for service qubes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/disposable-customization.rst:92
#: 5b222dd38c0f4e2297146d0fd2a55041
msgid ""
"You can use a :term:`named disposable` for service qubes (such as those "
"with the ``sys-*`` naming scheme) as long as they are stateless. For "
"example, a ``sys-net`` using DHCP or ``sys-usb`` will work. In most cases"
" ``sys-firewall`` will also work, even if you have configured app qube "
"firewall rules. The only exception is if you require something like VM to"
" VM communication and have manually edited ``iptables`` or other items "
"directly inside the firewall app qube."
msgstr ""

